{"TopicId":143732,"ForumId":15,"TopicTitle":"Normalmaps and mipmapping","CreatedByName":"Galileo","CreatedById":150430,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-07-13T17:09:06Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"Galileo","CreatedById":150430,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-07-13T17:09:06Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSo I finally got my normalmaps to work correctly but I\u0027m noticing that it\u0027s very \u0022pixelated\u0022 \u00A0for lack of a better word. More like a scrambled TV at certain angles. I don\u0027t know if I need to use the mipmap fade option (Or mipmaps at all) or if I need to just tone down the detail of my normalmaps and turn up the blur slightly. \u00A0I plan on trying out what I can but if someone can point me in the right direction I would greatly appreciate it. \u00A0\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/75006-nathankell/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u002275006\u0022 href=\u0022%7B___base_url___%7D/index.php?/profile/75006-nathankell/\u0022 rel=\u0022external\u0022\u003E@NathanKell\u003C/a\u003E I have seen your name pop up in a few Google searches related to normalmaps and such. Have any pointers that could help me and potentially other out?\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222016-07-13T17:11:55Z\u0022 title=\u002207/13/2016 05:11  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00227 yr\u0022\u003EJuly 13, 2016\u003C/time\u003E by Berlin\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"nli2work","CreatedById":106805,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-07-13T20:46:55Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nuse higher res for normal maps. 1024 at least. you can get away with 512 if there aren\u0027t much small details.\u00A0Keep thin lines parallel or horizontal will help with the aliasing a lot.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Galileo","CreatedById":150430,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-07-13T22:22:48Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222674782\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022143732\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221468442815\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022106805\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022nli2work\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 hour ago, nli2work said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nuse higher res for normal maps. 1024 at least. you can get away with 512 if there aren\u0027t much small details.\u00A0Keep thin lines parallel or horizontal will help with the aliasing a lot.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAll of the normalmaps are 1024 and all lines are horizontal and vertical. Would blurring the NRM help? Or turning down the detail?\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"CobaltWolf","CreatedById":105588,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-07-13T22:39:35Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYou could try reducing the severity of the normal maps (ie bringing the contrast down and bringing things closet to 50% gray)\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Galileo","CreatedById":150430,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-07-13T22:44:11Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222674926\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022143732\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221468449575\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022105588\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022CobaltWolf\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nJust now, CobaltWolf said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYou could try reducing the severity of the normal maps (ie bringing the contrast down and bringing things closet to 50% gray)\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWhat do you mean? They export as grayscale for me and not a lot of contrast. \u00A0The only I can think of is my textures are too detailed which means little vertical and horizontal lines which cause aliasing\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"CobaltWolf","CreatedById":105588,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-07-13T22:44:58Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222674931\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022143732\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221468449851\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022150430\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Berlin\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nJust now, Berlin said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWhat do you mean? They export as grayscale for me and not a lot of contrast. \u00A0The only I can think of is my textures are too detailed which means little vertical and horizontal lines which cause aliasing\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nCan you post your normal map?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Galileo","CreatedById":150430,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-07-13T22:46:17Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAs soon as I get home I will\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Galileo","CreatedById":150430,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-07-14T00:13:35Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222674933\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022143732\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221468449898\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022105588\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022CobaltWolf\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 hour ago, CobaltWolf said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nCan you post your normal map?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ciframe class=\u0022imgur-album\u0022 frameborder=\u00220\u0022 height=\u0022550\u0022 src=\u0022//imgur.com/a/hC4Rt/embed?background=ffffff\u0026amp;text=1a1a1a\u0026amp;link=4e76c9\u0022 width=\u0022100%\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI fixed em. I had to turn the detail value down from 80% to 12%. looks really good!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"nli2work","CreatedById":106805,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-07-14T01:05:32Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\ndid you use Unity\u0027s generate normal from gray scale option? If so that would explain what you\u0027re getting and how you fixed it.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222016-07-14T01:06:23Z\u0022 title=\u002207/14/2016 01:06  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00227 yr\u0022\u003EJuly 14, 2016\u003C/time\u003E by nli2work\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Galileo","CreatedById":150430,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-07-14T01:10:26Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222675079\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022143732\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221468458332\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022106805\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022nli2work\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n4 minutes ago, nli2work said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\ndid you use Unity\u0027s generate normal from gray scale option? If so that would explain what you\u0027re getting and how you fixed it.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNo I\u0027m using Nvidias dds plugin for photoshop\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Gamax19","CreatedById":157766,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-07-14T09:10:52Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThanks for the fantastic tutorial it helped me out a ton.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Kartoffelkuchen","CreatedById":108501,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-07-14T13:00:06Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIn Unity, when setting the texture to \u0022normal map\u0022; there\u0027s a checkbox below, saying something like \u0022create from blablabla\u0022. Uncheck that and you\u0027ll be fine.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Gamax19","CreatedById":157766,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-07-15T11:33:06Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222675727\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022143732\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221468501206\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022108501\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Kartoffelkuchen\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n22 hours ago, Kartoffelkuchen said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIn Unity, when setting the texture to \u0022normal map\u0022; there\u0027s a checkbox below, saying something like \u0022create from blablabla\u0022. Uncheck that and you\u0027ll be fine.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThanks I was wondering that myself.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}